### ⚙️ Graceful Shutdown

For enhanced robustness, `Node Locksmith` provides built-in support for gracefully shutting down your application. Why is this important? Without cleaning up resources like lock files, a terminated application can leave behind a "ghost" lock, preventing new instances from starting. Our termination handling ensures that your lock file is cleaned up properly no matter how the application is closed.

Here’s how you can implement graceful shutdown handling in your application:

```javascript
// All other imports and code setup...

// Start your app with LockManager in control
main().catch(handleTermination);

// This function defines how to handle a graceful shutdown
async function handleTermination(error) {
    // Log any errors if present
    if (error) {
        logger.error('Error during termination:', error);
    }

    // Remove the lock to allow future instances
    await lockManager.removeLock();
    logger.info('Application has been terminated gracefully.');

    // Necessary for handling asynchronous cleanup
    process.exit(error ? 1 : 0);
}

// Attach the handleTermination function to process termination signals
process.on('exit', handleTermination);
process.on('SIGINT', handleTermination);
process.on('SIGTERM', handleTermination);
```

By integrating these few lines, you ensure that `Node Locksmith` will make your shutdown process just as safe and reliable as your startup process!

